addr="marcelofiore">Marcelo Fiore</fr:link></fr:contributor></fr:authors></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter><fr:p>For <fr:link
href="jms-00LX.xml"
type="local"
addr="jms-00LX">finite sets</fr:link> <fr:tex>A</fr:tex> and <fr:tex>B</fr:tex>, we can describe number of <fr:link
href="jms-00MO.xml"
type="local"
addr="jms-00MO">injections</fr:link> from <fr:tex>A</fr:tex> to <fr:tex>B</fr:tex> as follows:</fr:p><fr:tex
display="block">   \mathord { \# } { \mathrm {Inj} { \mathopen {} \left ( A , B \right ) \mathclose {}} } =   \begin {cases}   { \mathord { \# } {B} \choose \mathord { \# } {A}} \cdot   { \mathopen {} \left ( \mathord { \# } {A} \right ) \mathclose {}} ! &amp; \text {when }  \mathord { \# } {A} \leq   \mathord { \# } {B}    \\    0 &amp; \text {otherwise}   \end {cases} </fr:tex>
 
   
